  "abstract": "Fusarium wilt (FW), caused by Fusarium oxysporum f sp\r\nciceris, is an important and widespread soilborne disease\r\nof chickpea (Cicer arietinum) in the Terai and inner Terai\r\nof Nepal (Pandey et al. 2000). In Nepal, wilt is more\r\ncommon in chickpea following rice (Oryza sativa) crop\r\nand occurs throughout the growing season of the crop.",
